========================================================================
  GOLD 1H BACKTEST v2  —  Improvements over v1:
  [1] 1H interval  -> full year of data (730 days available)
  [2] EMA200 trend filter -> no counter-trend trades
  [3] Session filter 08:00-21:00 UTC -> liquid hours only
  [4] R:R 2.0 (was 1.5) -> break-even drops from 40% to 33%
  [5] RSI thresholds 35/65 (was 40/60) -> cleaner entries
  [6] Max 2 consecutive losses/day -> drawdown protection
  [7] BB width percentile filter (< 25.0th pct blocked)
  [8] Spread/slippage model (2.5 pips / $0.25)
  [9] Daily-equity-curve Sharpe (replaces per-trade Sharpe)
  [10] Walk-forward split 70/30 train/val
  [11] ADX(14) filter: EMA_MACD_TREND_SELL needs ADX >= 25
  [12] BB_RSI lower confluence threshold (2/5)
  [13] Monthly drawdown brake (halve lot when month P&L < -$150)
  [BE] Breakeven move at +1.0R -> SL to entry +/- $0.50
  Period: 2y (725 days)
